claim.claim-text:
1. A method for forming a semiconductor memory cell array structure, comprising: 
providing a vertical MOSFET DRAM cell structure having a deposited polysilicon layer planarized to a top surface of a trench top oxide in an array trench of a silicon substrate; 
forming a shallow trench isolation oxide region along said array trench; 
etching said polysilicon layer selective to a nitride layer on said silicon substrate to form one or more silicon nitride spacers between a bitline diffusion region and a vertical gate polysilicon region, and between said shallow trench isolation oxide region and said vertical gate polysilicon region; and 
depositing a gate stack structure over said vertical gate polysilicon region and between said one or more silicon nitride spacers to form a borderless contact between said gate stack structure and said bitline diffusion region, and said shallow trench isolation oxide region.

3. The method of claim 1, wherein said deposition further comprises 
depositing a polysilicon layer on said nitride layer; 
blanket recessing said polysilicon layer; 
depositing a gate stack and a gate cap nitride to form said gate stack structures between said silicon nitride spacers on said vertical gate polysilicon region; 
patterning said gate stack structure; 
forming one or more silicon nitride spacers on one or more sidewalls of said gate stack structure, wherein said silicon nitride spacers contact said silicon nitride spacers of said vertical gate polysilicon regions; and 
etching said trench top oxide to expose said silicon substrate and said bitline diffusion region.

8. A method for forming a semiconductor memory cell array structure, comprising: 
providing a vertical MOSFET DRAM cell structure having a deposited polysilicon layer planarized to a top surface of a trench top oxide in an array trench of a silicon substrate; 
forming a shallow trench isolation oxide region along said array trench; 
etching said polysilicon layer selective to a nitride layer on said silicon substrate; 
etching said nitride layer to form one or more silicon nitride spacers between a vertical gate polysilicon region and said shallow trench isolation region; 
depositing a second polysilicon layer on said nitride layer; 
blanket recessing said second polysilicon layer; 
depositing a gate stack and a gate cap nitride to form said gate stack structures between said silicon nitride spacers on said vertical gate polysilicon region; 
patterning said gate stack structure; 
forming one or more silicon nitride spacers on one or more sidewalls of said gate stack structure, wherein said silicon nitride spacers contact said silicon nitride spacers of said vertical gate polysilicon region; and 
etching said trench top oxide to expose said silicon substrate and said bitline diffusion region.

9. A method for forming a semiconductor memory cell array structure, comprising: 
providing a vertical MOSFET DRAM cell structure having a deposited polysilicon layer planarized to a top surface of a trench top oxide in an array trench of a silicon substrate; 
forming a shallow trench isolation oxide region along said array trench; 
isotropically removing said polysilicon layer selective to a nitride layer on said silicon substrate; 
anisotropically etching said nitride layer to form one or more silicon nitride spacers bordering a vertical gate polysilicon region of said silicon substrate, and located between said vertical gate polysilicon region and said shallow trench isolation regions; 
depositing a gate stack between said silicon nitride spacers on said vertical gate polysilicon region; 
depositing a gate cap nitride on said gate stack to form a gate stack structure; and 
forming one or more silicon nitride spacers on one or more sidewalls of said gate stack structure, wherein said silicon nitride spacers contact said silicon nitride spacers of said vertical gate polysilicon region and insulate said gate stack structure from said bitline diffusion region.

10. A vertical MOSFET structure used in forming dynamic random access memory, comprising: 
a gate stack structure comprising one or more silicon nitride spacers; 
a vertical gate polysilicon region disposed in an array trench, wherein said vertical gate polysilicon region comprises one or more silicon nitride spacers; 
a bitline diffusion region; 
a shallow trench isolation region bordering said array trench; and 
wherein said gate stack structure is disposed on said vertical gate polysilicon region such that said silicon nitride spacers of said gate stack structure and said vertical gate polysilicon region form a borderless contact with said bitline diffusion region and said shallow trench isolation region.
